Matrix model description 
	
In this section we study the matrix model of the gauge theory with
multi trace operators. As it was shown intaking the naively  including a multi trace operator as the 
potential of the corresponding matrix model would lead to an incorrect
result. And in fact we should work with the linearized form of the
superpotential. Therefore we consider  matrix model with 
the following cubic potential
W_tree =13 Tr (^3)+12 m'
Tr (^2)+Tr ()-gA_1A_2.
This can be thought of as a matrix model with the single trace potential
while treating 's as constant background fields plus a shift of the
form . For the single trace part, the potential has two critical 
point  and  such that
